AB  - This paper addresses some of the connections between Isaac Asimov's future history and utilitarian moral theory. Utilitarianism has long been plagued by a set of practical problems that render the act of calculating utilities problematic. Because one of the central themes of Asimov's future history is a utilitarian drive toward the greatest good for humanity, these same calculation problems create a hurdle for Asimov. I argue here that several of the major developments in Asimov's future history can be read as a series of attempts to produce a better solution to utilitarian calculation problems.
